Each formula_23 is measurable. Moreover formula_24. Still further, as each formula_23 is a simple function formula_26Hence by the monotone convergence theorem
formula_27

==Discussion==

The counting measure is a special case of a more general construction. With the notation as above, any function formula_28 defines a measure formula_7 on formula_30 via
formula_31
where the possibly uncountable sum of real numbers is defined to be the supremum of the sums over all finite subsets, that is, 
formula_32
Taking formula_33 for all formula_34 gives the counting measure. 

